<p>If I want to store the information returned by the query when calling the callback, should I make a deep copy of every parameter in <strong>argv</strong> or can I safely assume that sqlite3 won't free it after returning from the callback? I'm using C as programming language.</p>  <pre><code>static int callback_consult(void *dummy, int argc, char **argv, char **col_name) {   res_consult_t * answer = &amp;(global_answer -&gt; consult_res);   movie_t *curr_tuple = calloc(sizeof(char), sizeof(movie_t));    /* Should I memcpy ??? */   curr_tuple -&gt; name = argv[0];   curr_tuple -&gt; genre = argv[1];   curr_tuple -&gt; description = argv[2];   curr_tuple -&gt; seats_available = argv[3]; /* Convert to int */    (answer -&gt; movies)[tuple] = curr_tuple;    return SQLITE_OK; } </code></pre>